article.description: Eric Wilkes ran for 112 yards and two touchdowns, Helam Heimuli caught two touchdown passes and Weber State beat Idaho State 35-14 on Saturday.
article.headline: Weber State runs past Idaho State 35-14
article.linkText: Weber State runs past Idaho State 35-14
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- Eric Wilkes ran for 112 yards and two touchdowns, Helam Heimuli caught two touchdown passes and Weber State beat Idaho State 35-14 on Saturday. Weber State had 306 yards on the ground and held Idaho State to 310 total yards. The Wildcats scored the first 21 points. Treshawn Garrett had a short touchdown run, Heimuli made had a 4-yard TD catch and Wilkes scored on a 32-yard run. Heimuli added a 20-yard score in the third and Wilkes had a 2-yard TD in the fourth. Jadrian Clark was 12-of-23 passing for 138 yards with two touchdowns for Weber State (6-5, 5-3 Big Sky), which had a winning season for the first time since 2010. Emmanuel Pooler added 130 yards rushing. Michael Sanders threw for 219 yards and two touchdowns for Idaho State (2-9, 1-7). He had a 14-yard TD pass to Josh Cook and found Madison Mangum for an 11-yard score.
